<div class="card mt-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h1 class="card-title mb-3">What to do if you can't find your lease</h1>
    <p>
      We understand it can be frustrating that you cannot find your lease.
      Here are some things to check and consider.
    </p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">1. Check the tool's data freshness</h5>
    <p>On the <a href="/app">search page</a>, you'll see the date of the last successful monthly data import from HM Land Registry. This tells you when our dataset was last updated overall. It might be that you are looking for a lease that has recently been created or updated and it has not yet been include in the dataset available to us.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">2. Check your lease agreement</h5>
    <p>The lease you received when purchasing the property contains all key details, including the lease length start date.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">3. Consult your solicitor</h5>
    <p>If you used a solicitor when purchasing your home, they may still hold a record of your lease. They can provide detailed information about the lease terms and any legal implications related to the lease length.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">4. Contact your freeholder or Managing Agent</h5>
    <p>Your freeholder or property management company should have up-to-date records regarding your lease. They can confirm the remaining lease term and other key information.</p>

    <h5 class="mt-4">5. Request Information from the Land Registry</h5>
    <p>If you are unable to find information about your lease through this tool, you can
      <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/contact-hm-land-registry" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        contact HM Land Registry<span class="visually-hidden">(opens in a new tab)</span>
        <i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>
      </a>
    .</p>
  <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mt-3">
    <a href="<%= uid ? `/app/lease/${uid}` : '/app' %>" class="btn btn-secondary">
        Back to <%= uid ? 'Lease' : 'Search' %>
    </a>
  </div>
  </div>


</div>
